      "span_text": "It is fastacting, noninvasive, has minimal side effects, and can be applied in multiple forms, including massage, inhalation, compress, and baths with mineral and herbal substances. Aromatherapy was utilized in Egypt and India thousands of years ago as a remedy for different diseases, is now an established nursing practice in the United Kingdom, and has become increasingly popular in the United States. The precise mechanism of aromatherapy is currently unclear; it is presumed to act both physiologically and psychologically."
